Chang Mai has been a favorite for nearly two decades. Stuffed chicken wings, crispy spring rolls, grilled eggplant salad, green curry, massamun curry, pad thai, pad siew, any of their soups and salads, sooooo good! The flavors and textures are always well-balanced. 10 or so stalls for parking behind the restaurant, ample street parking. Staff is always so friendly and attentive. Ambiance is great. Dress up or down, enjoy Chiang Mai restaurant anytime!
If I didn't know I was in Honolulu, I would think I was eating at a nice restaurant in Chiang Mai, Thailand. Great food and service.
Everything here is so good.  They offer dine in and take out safely.

This is really authentic Thai place, well beyond our expectation. Ask any your favorite. They will try the best. We ordered pork stuffed fried chicken wing that is true five stars. We asked dranken noodle and laap, both not on the menu but they made them for us. Very clean, manu on your device with QC code reader, well isolated dine in tables. Thier heavy cotton seat mat with low height back is super confy. Price is surprisingly reasonable, less than $20 per person including decent tip. Even my college boy would come back with friends.

We got take out and I got the vegetarian Royal Tofu Soup in Coconut Milk. Very disappointing. The tofu is sour, the soup broth tastes basically of nothing, certainly no lemon grass or ginger.  The  vegetables are tough ends of celery stalks, the tough white ends of some leafy green vegetable with no leafy green part...there's a few bits of carrot, some canned mushrooms...  Whoever made this soup did not care, and did not make any effort to make it tasty or have any nice things to eat in it. What a waste of time and money. I'm throwing it all away.

Fantastic Thai food and affordably priced. We had the pork pad ki mao and the pork panang curry. Portions were perfectly sized. Kevin was our fabulous waiter and the service was excellent from all staff. I wanted for nothing. Found my go to Thai spot.

This is a lovely Thai restaurant located in a very easy to see building on South King St. in Mo'ili'ili area, near the University of Hawaii.  It is has pleasant décor with Thai influences that really get you into the feel of the place and matches the food.  Very good assortment of Thai classics and a large vegetarian selections for those that are on a plant based diet.  Everything comes beautifully plated when served.  The service is also excellent there.  Everyone is smiling and greet you upon entry.  Their is constant attention to service there and it seems very sincere .  Although being a meat eater, I was in an extra healthy mode the day I went and ordered the Chiang Mai's Evil Tofu with brown Thai rice.  It was excellent.  Didn't even miss not having meat at all.  The dish was perfectly cooked and exploding with flavor.  I really appreciated that when I requested the spice level to be "Thai Hot" that they actually did it.  Most places still back off on the spice when they see someone that is Caucasian.  This is a great place for a date or a small group.  It has a really good feel to the place and plan to go back again.  I do recommend trying this place if you are in the area.

This is really head and shoulders above all the moderately priced thai resturants I have been to in the general area from University Ave to kalihi. For true foodies the balance of flavors  is just perfect. There is good and then there is close your eyes while they roll back into your head good. Chiang Mai never fails to make my heart sing.
It was ok
Great service. Food on very greasy side.

Best thai I've found on the island. Their veggie curry has the most diversity of ingredients around, which I value and definitely brings a lot to the dish. They pride themselves on their sticky rice for good reason! Also the best pad thai around, it's way more complex and rich in flavor than what other places dish out.
This has been my favorite Thai restaurant for the past twenty or so years. Always come here when I visit home.

We have been going to Chiang Mai on and off for at least 20 years.  It is a very pale shadow of what it used to be.  We will not be going there again.  The last 3 times we ordered our favorite dish, the snapper in chilli sauce, it was very disappointing.  We kept on hoping it was bad luck. Not the last time.  The fish was dry and smelled like it had been frozen too long.  The only excuse offered was to take it off the bill.  20 years of good will down the drain.

We had read that Kevin was a very helpful waiter on many of the reviews and we couldn’t agree more.  He helped us order based on our tastes and was so pleasant and fun. Chiang Mai Thai Cuisine is a pleasant, unpretentious restaurant with very good and authentic Thai food.  The atmosphere here isn't too formal in spite of the white tablecloths they use. The service at this restaurant was excellent. We ordered the spicy tofu (à la carte veggie menu) and fish filet with chili (special menu). We got 1 brown rice and 1 sticky rice to go with these--why not mix it up, right??? The rice came in reasonable, non-gigantic, portions. In particular, the sticky rice they have here is amazing and it comes in a little basket which is cool. I would love to see coconut rice on the menu (someday maybe?). Both of our dishes were spicy and tasted good. I preferred the tofu to the fish filet they had that day. The fish in our chili fish filet did not taste fresh or good to me because it was not firm and had little flavor -- I will definitely order the market price fish when I come back here. A basic selection of wine and beer is available but the better wine is all sold by the bottle and beer is bottle only. I do not think they use the small bar in the dining room for seating customers.  It looks like they have a small parking lot, but you'll mostly be parking on King Street.
